    "falklands_1982": {
      "label": "Falklands 1982 (Operation CORPORATE, British Task Force, South Atlantic)",
      "source": "Payne (1983); Jolly (2018); Blood, Zouris & Rotblatt (1998) FORECAS Table A.8",
      "notes": "Casualty generation rates (generators), priority distribution, DNBI composition, surgery/evacuation probabilities, and transport time distributions are NOT overridden here because the base env_data.json values are already Falklands-sourced (FORECAS Table A.8 combat WIA/KIA rates; FORECAS pp22-23 and Izaguirre et al. (2025) for DNBI composition) rather than generic or modern-era artifacts. Only the DOW ceiling and treatment-efficacy factors are overridden: the base values for those two groups are OIF/OEF-era (TCCC, damage control resuscitation/surgery), which did not exist as doctrine in 1982, so applying them to a Falklands scenario would misattribute modern treatment technique for the low historical DOW rate. See README 'Scenario Profiles' section.",
